Package jchrest.domainSpecifics.fixations

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AheadOfAgentFixation
    A Fixation that, when constructed, will return the Square that is 1 Square north of the result of invoking Scene.getLocationOfCreator().
    CentralFixation
    A Fixation that, when constructed, will suggest either the absolute centre Square of a Scene to fixate on or, if there is no absolute centre in the Scene passed to #this#make(jchrest.domainSpecifics.Scene, int) (either Scene.getHeight() or Scene.getWidth() for the Scene passed to #this#make( jchrest.domainSpecifics.Scene, int) returns an even number), a Square around the absolute centre is returned.
    HypothesisDiscriminationFixation
    Represents a Fixation made using the "hypothesis-discrimination" heuristic (see "Perception and Memory in Chess" by de Groot and Gobet, section 8.7.6).
    PeripheralItemFixation
    Represents a Fixation that should be made on a peripheral Square in a Scene that is not empty/blind/occupied by the agent that constructed the Scene.
    PeripheralSquareFixation
    Represents a Fixation that should be made on a peripheral Square in a Scene that is not blind/occupied by the agent that constructed the Scene.
